Jan 29, 2025
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.B. 14
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE BILL DRS15015-LUye-7
Short Title: Constitutional Amendment/Repeal Literacy Test. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Hanig, Hise, and Moffitt (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO AMEND THE NORTH CAROLINA CONSTITUTION TO REPEAL THE
3 LITERACY TEST REQUIREMENT.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. Section 4 of Article VI of the North Carolina Constitution is repealed.
6 SECTION 2. The amendment set out in Section 1 of this act shall be submitted to
7 the qualified voters of the State at the statewide general election to be held on November 3, 2026,
8 which election shall be conducted under the laws governing elections at that time. The question
9 to be used in the voting systems and ballots shall be:
10 "[ ] FOR [ ] AGAINST
11 Constitutional amendment to repeal the requirement that every person presenting
12 himself for registration shall be able to read and write any section of the Constitution in the
13 English language."
14 SECTION 3. The State Board of Elections shall certify the results of the referendum
15 conducted under Section 2 of this act. If a majority of votes cast on the question are in favor of
16 the amendment set out in Section 1 of this act, the Secretary of State shall enroll the amendment
17 among the permanent records of that office. If a majority of votes cast on the question are against
18 the amendment set out in Section 1 of this act, the amendment shall have no effect.
19 SECTION 4. If the certification from the State Board of Elections under Section 3
20 of this act reflects that a majority of votes cast on the question are in favor of the amendment set
21 out in Section 1 of this act, the amendment set out in Section 1 of this act is effective upon
22 certification.
23 SECTION 5. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
24 law.
*DRS15015-LUye-7*

